# Implementation Plan - Final Industrialization & Forensic Refinement

This plan outlines the final forensic and aesthetic refinements to the ICS Border Control System. The goal is to ensure the system is transition-ready, featuring a high-fidelity public gateway and a hardened administrative command center with real-time intelligence transparency.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> The "Security Incident" tracking will now elevate confirmed biometric conflicts to a dedicated supervisor dashboard. This ensures that identity theft or document forgery attempts are not just logged but actively flagged for interdiction.

> [!TIP]
> We will enhance the "Public Enrollment" process with a simulated "Neural Quality Check" for uploaded photos to simulate advanced biometric capturing standards.

## Proposed Changes

### 1. Administrative Hardening & Forensic Logic

#### [MODIFY] [server.js](file:///c:/Users/Mohammed/.gemini/antigravity/ics-backend/server.js)
- Enhance `calculateRiskScore` to include:
  - **Station Proximity**: Flag if the traveler's point of entry is significantly different from their last known crossing within a short timeframe.
  - **Watchlist Depth**: Categorize watchlist hits into "Observational" vs "Interdiction Required".
- Update `/api/mission-feed` to prioritize "Critical Risk" events.

#### [MODIFY] [ApplicationReview.jsx](file:///c:/Users/Mohammed/.gemini/antigravity/ics-frontend/src/pages/ApplicationReview.jsx)
- Add **Risk Factor Tags** to the application rows (e.g., "Frequent Crosser", "Watchlist Sensitivity").
- In the detail drawer, implement a **"Forensic Evidence Link"** that shows why a risk score was generated (e.g., "Matched signature with archived passport ETH-442").

### 2. Public Portal Excellence

#### [MODIFY] [Apply.jsx](file:///c:/Users/Mohammed/.gemini/antigravity/ics-frontend/src/pages/public/Apply.jsx)
- Implement a **"Biometric Capture Simulation"** during the photo upload step.
- Add "Industrial Grade" validation feedback (e.g., "Document Resolution Verified", "Biometric Signature Extracted").

#### [MODIFY] [Status.jsx](file:///c:/Users/Mohammed/.gemini/antigravity/ics-frontend/src/pages/public/Status.jsx)
- Enhance the status display with a professional **"Clearance Progress"** bar showing the adjudication stages (Encryption -> Forensic Check -> Officer Review -> Issuance).

### 3. Visual & Aesthetic Refinement

#### [MODIFY] [Dashboard.jsx](file:///c:/Users/Mohammed/.gemini/antigravity/ics-frontend/src/pages/Dashboard.jsx)
- Integrate a **"Global Security Level"** indicator (Alpha, Bravo, Charlie, Delta) based on recent watchlist hits and system anomalies.
- Refine the **"Hardware Telemetry"** widget to include "System Latency" and "Capture Node" status.

## Open Questions

- Should the "Global Security Level" be manually set by an Administrator, or should it automatically escalate based on a rolling 24-hour anomaly count? (Proposing automatic with manual override).

## Verification Plan

### Automated Tests
- `new-crossing-flow`: Process a new crossing and verify the `mission-feed` updates in real-time with the correct risk priority.
- `biometric-conflict-test`: Use passport `ETH-902123` to trigger a known conflict and verify the "Forensic Evidence" UI displays correctly.

### Manual Verification
1. Access the Public Portal and complete an application, observing the "Biometric Capture" feedback.
2. Log in as an Administrator and verify the "Global Security Level" reflects recent activity.
3. Review an application in `ApplicationReview` and ensure the Risk Factor tags are visible and accurate.
